node.title: Live: New case in Kaitaia, Health Minister admits home isolation 'wasn't ready' to cope with surge in daily cases
node.content: ["Kaitaia recorded a new case of COVID-19 late on Wednesday night, bringing the total number of infections in Northland to 29.", "Northland District Health Board said interviews are underway and mre information is expected on Thursday morning. The new case comes ahead of upper Northland's pending return to a lower level of restrictions, with it set to join the majority of the country at alert level 2 at 11:59pm on Thursday.", "There were 147 new cases of the virus recorded on Wednesday - 131 in Auckland, 14 in Waikato and two in Northland. Eighty-one people are in hospital, with 11 in intensive care or high dependency units.\u00a0\n", "In other developments, students in alert level 3 will be able to return to the classroom next week, with Years 1 to 8 starting on a part-time basis. The Astra-Zeneca vaccine will be made available as an alternative to those who medically cannot have Pfizer-BioNTech, and retail has officially reopened in Auckland under alert level 3, step 2.", "Follow Newshub's live updates below - app users, click here", "7:15am - Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live coverage of the COVID-19 outbreak for November 11, 2021."]
